    "comp": null,
    "perFrameCode": [
      "/*",
      "Conditional Ternary Operation on MilkDrop!",
      "",
      "The general form is expcond ? valtrue : valfalse",
      "Which:",
      "- expcond is condition expression, for example val1 > val2, x == y etc.",
      "- valtrue is the value when it's true",
      "- valfalse is the value when it's false",
      "",
      "",
      "This expression can be used like:",
      "*/",
      "",
      "q1 = time%2 == 0 ? 1 : 0;",
      "",
      "/*",
      "Which reduces the use of if(cond(val1, val2), valtrue, valfalse);.",
      "For example: this expression verifies if time variable is even, then it's true (1), else false (0) using conditional ternary operator, assigned to q1.",
      "The expression used above is equivalent to if(equal(time%2, 0), 1, 0) or if(time%2, 1, 0).",
      "",
      "You can also use the assignation trick, such as:",
      "*/",
      "",
      "//q1 = boolstate = time%2 == 0 ? 1 : 0; //DON'T UNCOMMENT IF IT'S NECESSARY TO DO.",
      "",
      "/*",
      "Which it also assigns the same expression to q1 and boolstate variables at the same time.",
      "",
      "Hope you have found something useful!",
      "Written by DJ XcitMosphere/Se7enSlasher/Incubo_.",
      "",
      "Check my DJ Channel: DJ XcitMosphere on YouTube, Twitter/X and MixCloud!",
      "Also donate me on PayPal for my DJ work. ;)",
      "*/",
      "wave_a = 0;",
      "monitor = q1; //Just for a test. Remove this line if you want."
    ],
